hopobject.body: I'd like a phonecard, please pharma focus shivaji nagar The remotely piloted or directly piloted arguments, in the end, seem to set up a false dichotomy. There will probably always be a need for human pilots directly at the controls of some aircraft. But that doesn't mean that investments and experimentation shouldn't be used to develop advanced remotely piloted aircraft capable of undertaking dangerous missions, such as the suppression of enemy air defense systems or swarming and decoy attacks against future enemy air forces. Such a mixed investment strategy seems to be a prudent approach, particularly in an age of austere defense budgets.
